cechurch, London, Middlesex, England":"London, Middlesex, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Rainan","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Italian: from the feminine form of the medieval personal name <i>Raino</i>, of ancient Germanic origin (from <i>ragin</i> ‘counsel’; see   Raineri  ).","Italian: possibly also a habitational name from Raina (a place near Prazzo in Cuneo province).","Italian: possibly also a nickname from the dialect word <i>raina</i> ‘frog’ (compare   Rana  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Rainone","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Carlo, Pasquale, Rocco, Salvatore, Angelo, Nicola, Antonietta, Carmelo, Carmine, Constantino, Cosimo, Domenic.","Italian: from the oblique case of an ancient Germanic personal name formed with the element <i>ragin</i> ‘advice, counsel’, or from an augmentative of the medieval personal name <i>Raino</i> of the same origin (see   Raina  )."]},{"name":"Raineri","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Carlo, Angelo, Carmelo, Ciro, Gasper, Giovanni, Luciano, Milio, Nicola, Sal, Vincenzo.","Italian (Sicily): from <i>Raineri</i>, a variant of <i>Rainero</i>, or a patronymic or plural form of <i>Rainero</i>, from ancient Germanic <i>Raginhari</i>, from <i>ragin</i> ‘counsel’ + <i>hari</i>, <i>heri</i> ‘army’."]}]},{"name":"Martha","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, of Aramaic rather than Hebrew origin, meaning ‘lady’. It was borne by the sister of Lazarus and Mary of Bethany (John 11:1). According to Luke 10:38, when Jesus visited the house of Mary and Martha, Mary sat at his feet, listening to him, while Martha ‘was cumbered about much serving’, so that she complained to Jesus, ‘Lord, dost thou not care that my sister hath left me to serve alone?’ For this reason, the name <i>Martha</i> has always been associated with hard domestic work, as opposed to the contemplative life."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705207,"age":5,"year":"1585","julianDay":2299970,"title":"The First English Colony is Established in America","description":"England established its first colony in North America in 1585 as a way to generate additional wealth. The colony was named Virginia, after the virgin Queen Elizabeth I.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705208,"age":7,"year":"1587","julianDay":2300700,"title":"Elizabeth I Signs Death Warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots","description":"Elizabeth I signed the death warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots, on February 1, 1587, as she was found guilty of plotting to assasinate Elizabeth. Mary, Queen of Scots, was beheaded at Fotheringhay Castle in England on February 8, 1587.","url":"https://www.elizabethi.org/mary_queen_of_scots/","urlTitle":"Elizabeth I.org - Mary Queen of Scots","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705210,"age":20,"year":"1600","julianDay":2305448,"title":"The Honourable East India Company","description":"The Honourable East India Company, a British joint-stock company, was established in 1600 for trade in the Indian Ocean region. At its height, the British East India Company had a private army which was twice the size of the British Army, ruled large sections of India, and revenues in the millions.","url":"https://www.historic-uk.com/HistoryUK/HistoryofEngland/The-East-India-Company/","urlTitle":"Historic UK - The East India Company","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Martha Rainan was born in 1580, in Saint Dunstan and All Saints Church, Stepney, London, England, United Kingdom, her father, Roger Rainam, was 3 and her mother, Mary Bartholomew, was 14. She married William Carter on 15 October 1599, in Stepney, Middlesex, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1605, in Westminster, London, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 25, and was buried in London, Middlesex, England."},"et":{"1580–1605":"1580–1605","1574–1605":"1574–1